The paper discusses the recent developments in Ant Colony Optimization (ACO) algorithms, which is a subfield of Swarm Intelligence. Swarm Intelligence is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI), which makes cs.AI a likely category. ACO algorithms are also used for optimization problems, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. The paper also discusses hybridization and parallel architectures, which are related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the application of ACO algorithms to various optimization problems, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category as well.
